[30;1m171 | [0m[35mn Andrychowicz et al., "Hindsight[0m
[30;1m172 | [0m[35m    Experience Replay" (https://arxiv.org/abs/1707.01495).  This is a method that can enormously[0m
[30;1m173 | [0m[35m    accelerate learning when rewards are very rare.  It requires that the environment state contains[0m
[30;1m174 | [0m[35m    information about the goal the agent is trying to achieve.  Each time it generates a rollout, it[0m
[30;1m175 | [0m[35m    processes that rollout twice: once using the actual goal the agent was pursuing while generating[0m
[30;1m176 | [0m[35m    it, and again using the final state of that rollout as the goal.  This guarantees that half of[0m

[30;1m5644 | [0m[35m    3. Step 3 finally aggregates {mji} to update the node-level embedding hi.[0m
[30;1m5645 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m81 | [0m[35m    (https://openai-public.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/blog/2017-07/ppo/ppo-arxiv.pdf).[0m
[30;1m82 | [0m[35m    This class requires the policy to output two quantities: a vector giving the probability of[0m
[30;1m83 | [0m[35m    taking each action, and an estimate of the value function for the current state.  It[0m
[30;1m84 | [0m[35m    optimizes both outputs at once using a loss that is the sum of three terms:[0m
[30;1m85 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m86 | [0m[35m    1. The policy loss, which seeks to maximize the discounted reward for each action.[0m
[30;1m87 | [0m[35m    2. The value loss, which tries to make the value estimate match the actual discounted reward[0m

[30;1m138 | [0m[35mdef _get_atom_scopes(graph_index: ArrayLike) -> List[List[int]]:[0m
[30;1m139 | [0m[35m    """Atom scope is a list of tuples with a single entry for every[0m
[30;1m140 | [0m[35m    molecule in the batched graph. The entry indicates the beginning[0m
[30;1m141 | [0m[35m    node index for a molecule and the number of nodes in the molecule.[0m

[30;1m21 | [0m[35m    model.[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    The batching method takes in a dc.feat.GraphData object created by[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m    GroverFeaturizer. New node indices and edge indices are[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m    computed by stacking the adjacency matrices of the graphs diagonally[0m

[30;1m2140 | [0m[35m        The algorithm used for this complete shuffle is O(N^2) where N is the[0m

[30;1m468 | [0m[35m    graph_distance of one another. This is done by using the fact that the[0m

[30;1m2028 | [0m[35m    Binary Alignment Map (BAM) is the comprehensive raw data of genome[0m
[30;1m2029 | [0m[35m    sequencing. It consists of the lossless, compressed binary representation[0m
[30;1m2030 | [0m[35m    of the Sequence Alignment Map files. BAM files are smaller and more[0m

[30;1m52 | [0m[35m    This class requires the policy to output two quantities: a vector giving the probability of[0m
[30;1m53 | [0m[35m    taking each action, and an estimate of the value function for the current state.  It[0m
[30;1m54 | [0m[35m    optimizes both outputs at once using a loss that is the sum of three terms:[0m
[30;1m55 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m56 | [0m[35m    1. The policy loss, which seeks to maximize the discounted reward for each action.[0m
[30;1m57 | [0m[35m    2. The value loss, which tries to make the value estimate match the actual discounted reward[0m
